:<div>

blossom /ˈblɒsəm/

(blossoming,blossomed,blossoms) 

1. N-VAR Blossom is the flowers that appear on a tree before the fruit. (果树的) 花 

例： The cherry blossom came out early in Washington this year. 华盛顿的樱花今年开得早。 

2. V-I If someone or something blossoms , they develop good, attractive, or successful qualities. 成功发展 

例： Why do some people take longer than others to blossom? 为什么有些人比其他人大器晚成呢？ 

例： What began as a local festival has blossomed into an international event. 开始时的一个地方节日已经发展成了一个国际盛会。 

3. V-I When a tree blossoms , it produces blossom. (树) 开花 

例： Rain begins to fall and peach trees blossom. 雨开始下，桃树就开花了。

